text: Mount Damavand is the tallest mountain in Iran and Western Asia, and the tallest volcano in Asia, and the third tallest volcano in the Eastern Hemisphere (after Mount Kilimanjaro and Mount Elbrus), at in total elevation. Mount Damavand is a dormant volcano in northern Iran about northeast of Iran's capital city of Tehran. Category:Mountains of Asia Category:Volcanoes of Asia Category:Mazandaran Province
